replies.body:
Because he is a paradox champion. 

And what I mean by that is, if he is on your team you lose and if he is on the enemy team he carries.

People (stupid ass junglers especially) fail to realize that all he has to do is press W and a gank is 100% successful.
Also, he needs a competent team to not die every fucking 10 seconds to be useful. 

Somehow though, when you play as him or with him on your team, your team thinks, "oh he is good he will carry just let him stack lol, and let me die 10 times just to be of some help to him."

A pushing/pushed  nasus will get ganks if he is on the enemy team but will literally be ignored if he is on your own team.

Other examples of Paradox Champions include:

{{champion:81}} 
{{champion:92}}
{{champion:157}} 
{{champion:67}} 
{{champion:238}} 

Meaning: If they are on the enemy team, they are pros, if they are on yours, they feed and make the game 4v5.
